      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THREETWONINE (3) resumes after finishing fourth at her latest appearance at Penrith on October 23. Talented and has plenty of upside. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. This doesn't look as hard so she is sure to prove tough to beat. LORD JAYDO (2) has been racing well of late. Finished third at his latest appearance over 1609m at this track, beaten 4 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a comparable field and he can take this out. RONNYS WATCHING (8) comes right into contention after scoring last start by a neck at this track over 1609m. A LITTLE DILEMMA (4) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished eighth last start over 1980m at Tamworth, coming home 14 metres from the winner. Only needs to get things right to be in the money.",
